The Delta State Police Command Tuesday, confirmed the death of Nollywood actor, Prince Abuchi Ikpo who was found dead in his Asaba apartment in Delta State. The Police Public Relations Officer in the State, DSP Bright Edafe confirmed that the actor was killed in his house and locked up till his body was found. “The body was found at his apartment near Jesus Save area, Asaba, on Monday. “They killed him and locked the dead body inside the house. “No much details on this yet,” the PPRO said.   The Police Command in Akwa Ibom has confirmed the arrest of Mo ses Armstrong, a member of Actors Guild of Nigeria for alledgedly raping a minor. The State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Odiko Macdon, confirmed this in a statement to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Uyo… In "News" A businessman , Lawrence Olorungbon, his wife and three children have been found dead in thier apartment in Apapa area of Lagos. In "Metro" As residents of Anambra State were still weighing in on the likely impact of Governor Chukwuma Soludo's weekend visit to the detained leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, Nnamdi Kanu, gunmen struck in three locations in parts of the state yesterday. In "Metro"